"<div class=\"announce instapaper_body md\" data-path=\"README.md\" id=\"file\"><article class=\"markdown-body entry-content\" itemprop=\"text\"><h1><a href=\"#double-bufferjs\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\" id=\"user-content-double-bufferjs\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>double-buffer.js</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/gaggle/double-buffer.js\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/a0d3c8bc906fc1c9298f3327658c06833e83814c/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f676167676c652f646f75626c652d6275666665722e6a732e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\" alt=\"Build Status\" data-canonical-src=\"https://travis-ci.org/gaggle/double-buffer.js.svg?branch=master\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://coveralls.io/github/gaggle/double-buffer.js?branch=master\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://camo.githubusercontent.com/d617281f722bccf9afc8245d71cc51b3e58bbcc6/68747470733a2f2f636f766572616c6c732e696f2f7265706f732f6769746875622f676167676c652f646f75626c652d6275666665722e6a732f62616467652e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\" alt=\"Coverage Status\" data-canonical-src=\"https://coveralls.io/repos/github/gaggle/double-buffer.js/badge.svg?branch=master\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>\n<p>Smoothly load images sequentially.</p>\n<p>An image is first pre-loaded, then faded in on the front buffer.\nOnce fully shown it's swapped to live permanently on the back buffer.\nAt this point a new image can be faded in, leading to smooth fadein transitions.</p>\n<p>Useful for galleries or backgrounds displaying potentially infinite images.</p>\n<p>Here an inital image fades in, and another immediately fades in on top.\n<a href=\"example.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"example.gif\" alt=\"Example\" style=\"max-width:100%;\"></a></p>\n<h3><a href=\"#install\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\" id=\"user-content-install\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install</h3>\n<pre><code>npm install gaggle/double-buffer.js\n</code></pre>\n<h3><a href=\"#use\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\" id=\"user-content-use\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Use</h3>\n<pre><code>var DoubleBuffer = require(\"double-buffer.js\")\nbuffer = new DoubleBuffer(parent, undefined, {duration: 1000})\nbuffer.set(\"./clouds.jpg\")\n</code></pre>\n</article></div>"